After the closure of [[PrimeTime Radio]] in 2006, the original licence was amended to allow the launch of a new classic and contemporary jazz service, [[theJazz]] which was launched on  [[December 25]], [[2006]], before the [[December 31]], [[2006]] deadline set in the licence amendment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofcom.org.uk/static/radiolicensing/digital/formats/DN001.doc|title=ANNEX - PART I - Conditions relating to simulcast services and digital sound programme services|accessdate=2007-05-12|publisher=Ofcom|format=doc}}</ref>

=== Local and regional ensembles ===

The Radio Authority (and subsequently Ofcom) continue to reward regional ensemble licences to a number of radio groups with advertising of the licences starting from 1998,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofcom.org.uk/static/archive/rau/radio-stations/digital/dm-main.html|title= Browse directory of Digital Multiplexes|accessdate=2007-05-05|publisher=Radio Authority|work=Ofcom}}</ref> and licence awards being awarded from May 10, 1999, with the Birmingham ensemble being the first local licence being issued to CE Digital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofcom.org.uk/static/archive/rau/newsroom/news-release/99/pr072.htm|title=RADIO AUTHORITY AWARDS FIRST LOCAL DIGITAL MULTIPLEX LICENCE, FOR BIRMINGHAM|accessdate=2007-05-05|date=1999-15-10|publisher=Radio Authority|work=Ofcom}}</ref> The Birmingham ensemble licence award was followed by awards for licences in [[Manchester]], [[Greater London]], [[Glasgow]] and [[South Yorkshire]], with more licences being awarded afterwards.

The first regional licence<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wohnort.demon.co.uk/DAB/uknat.html|title=DAB Ensembles Worldwide - United Kingdom & the Isle of Man|accessdate=2007-05-05}}</ref> to cover a greater area of land compared to a local ensemble was awarded on October 6, 2000 to Switch Digital for Central Scotland<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofcom.org.uk/static/archive/rau/newsroom/news-release/00/pr140.htm|title=RADIO AUTHORITY AWARDS LOCAL DIGITAL MULTIPLEX LICENCE FOR CENTRAL SCOTLAND|accessdate=2007-05-05|date=2000-10-06|publisher=Radio Authority|work=Ofcom}}</ref> Other areas which were awarded and classed as regional licences include:

