=== Second national ensemble ===

Ofcom announced in 2005 that they would be advertising for the second national digital ensemble. As a result, [[GCap Media|GCap]] threatened to take Ofcom to court after being told by the Radio Authority that there would not be another national ensemble. The court action was dropped after Ofcom assured GCap that none of the stations on the second ensemble would compete with existing stations on the Digital One ensemble.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalradiotech.co.uk/articles/GCap-bottle-out-of-taking-Ofcom-to-court.php|title=	
GCap bottle out of taking Ofcom to court|accessdate=2007-04-21|date=2006-03-30|publisher=Digital Radio Tech}}</ref>

On December 1, 2006, Ofcom advertised a licence for a second national digital ensemble to launch new digital radio and multimedia services on frequency block 11A (216.928 MHz)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofcom.org.uk/radio/ifi/rbl/dcr/adverts/advrt_national/national.pdf|title=Advertisement of National
Radio Multiplex Licence|accessdate=2007-04-21|date=2006-12-01|publisher=Ofcom|format=pdf}}</ref> Applications needed to be submitted to Ofcom by March 28, 2007.

On March 29, 2007, Ofcom announced that it had received two applications for the second national digital ensemble, from the [[4 Digital Group]] and [[National Grid Wireless]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofcom.org.uk/media/news/2007/03/nr_20070329a|title=Ofcom receives two applications for the DAB National Radio multiplex licence|accessdate=2007-04-15|date=2007-03-29|publisher=Ofcom}}</ref> The radio channels which made up both applications are as follows:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio-now.co.uk/news545.htm|title=Second UK-wide national DAB digital radio multiplex draws two applicants|accessdate=2007-05-05|date=2007-04-15|publisher=Radio-now.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/radio/4digital/services.html|title=The Services|accessdate=2007-05-05|publisher=4 Digital Group}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofcom.org.uk/radio/ifi/rbl/dcr/applications/app_national/national/|title=List of Applications for Radio Multiplex Licence: National|accessdate=2007-05-05|date=2007-03-30|publisher=Ofcom}}</ref>

