On July 6, 2007 Ofcom awarded the licence for the second national ensemble to the 4Digital Group, who are required to launch its services one year after its licence award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofcom.org.uk/media/news/2007/07/nr_20070706|title=4 Digital group awarded new national digital radio multiplex licence|date=2007-07-06|accessdate=2007-07-06|publisher=Ofcom}}</ref>

== Digital Radio Development Bureau ==

The Digital Radio Development Bureau (DRDB) is a trade body whose primary objective is to promote the use and take up of [[Digital Audio Broadcasting|DAB]] in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.drdb.org/index.php?internalPage=intro.php&internalHeaderPage=intro_hd.html|title=Welcome to the Digital Radio Development Bureau|accessdate=2007-04-21|publisher=Digital Radio Development Bureau}}</ref> DRDB's stakeholders include the [[BBC]], [[GCap Media]], [[Digital One]], [[EMAP]] and MXR.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.drdb.org/index.php?internalPage=part.php&internalHeaderPage=part_hd.html|title=Our Partners|accessdate=2007-04-21|publisher=Digital Radio Development Bureau}}</ref> Part of DRDB's plans to promote [[Digital Audio Broadcasting|DAB]] uptake is to set up a website for consumers as well as print and [[Radio commercial|radio advertising]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.drdb.org/index.php?internalPage=cons.php&internalHeaderPage=cons_hd.html|title=Consumers|accessdate=2007-04-21|publisher=Digital Radio Development Bureau}}</ref>

